data.text:
How to use Axis Bank Silapathar IFSC code in online fund transfer?

Axis Bank Silapathar IFSC code is an 11 digit code used in online fund transfers. This IFSC code contains 4 Characters that represent Axis Bank, 5th character is reserved for future use and the last 6 characters represent the Silapathar branch code. Axis Bank has many branches all over the country and physical cheques cannot be transferred anywhere across the country to transfer funds hence internet banking is preferred. The IFSC code UTIB0003827 is used to identify the Axis Bank Silapathar participating in online transactions via RTGS, IMPS and NEFT systems.
